Was going to go to Staples Center but opted for GNR again only to see Axl run out of steam after "only" 155 mins. I was scheduled for jury duty the next week throwing Anaheim Nov 6 into jeopardy but when I checked in and saw I didn't have to report Monday I decided to just go to San Diego.

Been wanting to see Doechii again ever since I saw her guest spot with Isiah Rashad 2 years ago and also been wanting to go to Viejas again since I saw The Who there and I must say she did not disappoint. Now hopefully there will be a headline tour soon. She came out on the hovercraft from Gentle Ben, like WTF.

The trip there was a bit harrowing with me hitting the arena only 40 mins before showtime, still ticketless with no good secondary site and box office options (aside from a whole empty row that just dropped at $199) also sorely lacking. Thankfully someone outside came thru for $80 at the last minute and I still wandered into the awesome seat. If I lived in SD I would go to pretty much everything here.

Doja Cat was great too but as much as I dig the recording, it's a very visual show.

Wanted to go to Anaheim again but since I brought my laptop with me I would have to go all the way home then backtrack to Anaheim, still a terrible arena, tickets so expensive and I pretty much ran out of energy. So glad I made the effort to go to this show, a total ten and top 5 of the year so far for sure.

Any Doechii pro shot / festival webcast video? Especially Coachella.

Also just Doechii at WeHo Pride and will get to it when I get to it.
